BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Vale’s New CEO Speaks, Mantega in Sao Paulo

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-05-20T03:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-20/brazil-daybook-vale-s-new-ceo-speaks-mantega-in-sao-paulo.html
Vale SA’s appointed Chief Executive
Officer Murilo Ferreira speaks to reporters in  Rio de Janeiro  at
12:30 p.m. Vale’s board yesterday approved Ferreira to replace
 Roger Agnelli . Chairman Ricardo Flores will also participate of
the press conference.  GOVERNMENT:
*President Dilma Rousseff has internal dispatches at 10 a.m.
*Finance Minister Guido Mantega meets with representatives of
the institute for retail development in  Sao Paulo  at 1 p.m.
*Central bank president Alexandre Tombini has closed-door
meeting in Sao Paulo.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Rio de Janeiro’s government auctions its state bank, Banco do
Estado do Rio de Janeiro, at 10 a.m. The state expects to raise
as much as 1 billion reais tomorrow with the sale.
*Cosan may release preliminary figures for the fiscal fourth
quarter, that ends March 31. The company usually releases
figures about 15 days before actual earnings, which are
scheduled for June 6.
*Embraer SA’s E-190 jets need more-frequent inspections after
tests turned up cracks that may indicate a structural flaw,
 Brazil ’s aviation authority said.  ECONOMY:
*Mid-month  consumer price index  at 9 a.m.  EQUITIES:
*CSN (CSNA3 BZ) buys Grupo AG’s Shares in three companies for
543 million euros
*Embraer (EMBR3 BZ) E-190 jets need checks for metal cracks,
Brazil says
*Banco do Brasil (BBAS3 BZ) sells $1.5 billion of 5.875%
subordinated bonds
*EDP to sell 19.9 million shares of Brazilian unit (ENBR3 BZ)  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index fell 0.8 percent to 62,367.36
*The real fell 0.4 percent to 1.6163 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
